    "text": "Erdős Problem #705: declared status 'disproved'. Formalized: yes. Let $G$ be a finite unit distance graph in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ (i.e. the vertices are a finite collection of points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ and there is an edge between two points if and only if the distance between them is $1$).\n\nIs there some $k$ such that if $G$ has girth $\\geq k$ (i.e. $G$ contains no cycles of length $<k$) then $\\chi(G)\\leq 3$? Prize: no. Tags: chromatic number, graph theory.",
